Text.Value: For a mere pittance of coin, I might summon the worthiest among them to lend aid to thy undertaking.
As thou desire.
Do you think I can trust these cultists?
Choose.
There is no one to dismiss.
I would like to dismiss [HirelingName_3_0b5f9e73-cec6-e308-15f4-8e142147908d].
Dost thou need my services?
Will these hirelings be joining me willingly?
Suspicion always haunts the guilty mind. My services are all that I can proffer thee. What thou wilt do with them is for thee to undertake.
Only thy leader may banish hirelings.
It is done.
Impossible. Thy party is full.
I would like to dismiss [HirelingName_2_c4187b58-a2f9-61d1-9899-e456945876fd].
For thy fate to be sealed, thou must take action.
Thou art at the threshold of thy destiny. Thou needst only to take thy last steps to cross it.
I would like to dismiss a hireling.
Patience. Thy colleague still peruses my ledger.
I would like to dismiss [HirelingName_1_03d3080c-4144-7335-8478-a4fb38a54eb9].
Never mind.
They bear great discontentment with their destiny.
Thou hast reached thy limit.
I would like to recruit a hireling. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_3_01f129ea-b4dc-44b6-8154-9a948f876a82])
No. Thy coinpurse is near empty.
Thou canst not hire allies. I must speak with thy leader.
Most willingly, forsooth. Their passions doth run deep for what hath been wrought upon them.
Beyond mortal realms, there doth exist an amalgamation of spirits akin to thine own, ensnared by the treacherous cult of the Absolute, felled in its name.
Leave.
If thou art ready, proceed to seal fate's image with thy final stitch.
Choose.
